oldstein born joseph leonard goldstein  april   age  kingstree south carolina fields biochemistry institutions university of texas southwestern medical center alma mater washington and lee university university of texas southwestern medical center known for cholesterol notable awards heinrich wieland prize  richard lounsbery award  louisa gross horwitz prize  nobel prize in physiology or medicine  william allan award  national medal of science  formemrs  website profilesutsouthwesterneduprofilejosephgoldsteinhtml joseph leonard goldstein born april   is an american biochemist he received the nobel prize in physiology or medicine in  along with fellow university of texas researcher michael brown for their studies regarding cholesterol they discovered that human cells have lowdensity lipoprotein ldl receptors that remove cholesterol from the blood and that when ldl receptors are not present in sufficient numbers individuals develop hypercholesterolemia and become at risk for cholesterol related diseases notably coronary heart disease their studies led to the development of statin drugs contents  life and career  awards  research papers  essays on the art of science  references  external links life and careeredit goldstein was born in kingstree south carolina the son of fannie alpert and isadore e goldstein who owned a clothing store goldstein received his bsci from washington and lee university in  and his md from texas universitys southwestern medical school in  upon completion of his residency goldstein moved to the national institutes of health nih in bethesda maryland where he worked in biochemical genetics in  goldstein relocated back to the southwestern medical center accepting a post as the head of the division of medical genetics at the southwestern medical center goldstein collaborated extensively with michael brown a fellow researcher at the center who had also worked at the nih from  to  goldstein and brown together published over one hundred major papers they are both listed in thomson reuters’ index of highly cited authors frequently mentioned as a candidate for nationallyprominent positions in scientific administration goldstein like his colleague michael brown chose to continue handson research in  their postdoctoral trainees wang xiaodong and michael briggs purified the sterol regulatory elementbinding proteins srebps a family of membranebound transcription factors since  goldstein brown and their colleagues have described the unexpectedly complex machinery that proteolytically releases the srebps from membranes thus allowing their migration to the nucleus where they activate all the genes involved in the synthesis of cholesterol and fatty acids the machinery for generating active srebps is tightly regulated by a negative feedback mechanism which explains how cells maintain the necessary levels of fats and cholesterol in the face of varying environmental circumstances goldstein is chair molecular genetics at university of texas southwestern medical center together goldstein and brown lead a research team that typically includes a dozen doctoral and postdoctoral trainees they have trained over  graduate students and postdoctoral fellows and five of their former postdoctoral fellows thomas c südhof wang xiaodong helen h hobbs david w russell and monty krieger have been elected to the us national academy of sciences former postdoctoral fellow thomas südhof received the  nobel prize in medicine or physiology and helen h hobbs received the  breakthrough prize in life sciences in  goldstein received a national medal of science in the field of molecular genetics and in  goldstein and brown won the albany medical center prize in medicine and biomedical research in recognition for their further work in understanding cholesterol and also the discovery of an insulinsensitive regulator which potentially could be used to develop treatments for diabetes mellitus goldstein is a member of the us national academy of sciences  and the institute of medicine and he was elected a foreign member of the royal society formemrs in  goldstein was appointed as chairman of the albert lasker medical research awards jury in  and was a recipient of the award ten years earlier since  goldstein has authored a series of essays on the deep relationship between art and science that appear in the annual nature medicine supplement that accompanies the lasker awards among his professional activities goldstein is a member of the board of trustees of the howard hughes medical institute and of the rockefeller university where he was elected as a life trustee in  he also serves as chairman of the board of scientific counselors of the broad institute and is a member of the board of directors of regeneron pharmaceuticals inc he previously served on the board of scientific governors of the scripps research institute a nonprofit institute that conducts biomedical research awardsedit joseph l goldstein has been awarded the following  – stadtman distinguished scientist award american society for biochemistry and molecular biology  – builders of science award researchamerica  – woodrow wilson awards for public service  – herbert tabor award american society for biochemistry and molecular biology  – albany medical center prize in medicine and biomedical research  – kober medal association of american physicians  – warren alpert foundation prize harvard medical school  – elected a foreign member of the royal society formemrs  – us national medal of science  – nobel prize in physiology or medicine  – albert lasker award for basic medical research  – william allan award american society of human genetics  – louisa gross horwitz prize columbia university  – gairdner foundation international award  – elected member of the national academy of sciences  – richard lounsbery award us national academy of sciences  – passano award johns hopkins university  – pfizer award in enzyme chemistry american chemical society research papersedi