bolism biography dr goldstein received a bs in chemistry from washington and lee university in  and his md from the university of texas southwestern medical center in  in  he received the nobel prize in physiology or medicine together with michael s brown for his research on the metabolism of low density lipoprotein ldl and has won numerous other awards for his contributions related to genetic diseases returning to the university of texas health science center in dallas in  now called ut southwestern medical center goldstein and his close colleague brown researched cholesterol metabolism and discovered that human cells have lowdensity lipoprotein ldl receptors that extract cholesterol from the bloodstream the lack of sufficient ldl receptors is the cause of familial hypercholesterolemia which predisposes heavily for cholesterolrelated diseases in addition to explaining the underlying pathology of the widelyobserved link between high levels of circulating cholesterol as ldl and coronary artery disease their work uncovered a previouslyunappreciated yet fundamental aspect of cell biology  receptormediated endocytosis in addition to contributing fundamentally to our understanding of how the cells in our bodies work drs goldstein and browns findings led to the development of statin drugs the cholesterollowering compounds that today are used by  million americans and are the most widely prescribed medications in the united states this crucial discovery is improving more lives every year new federal cholesterol guidelines are expected to triple the number of americans taking statin drugs to lower their cholesterol reducing the risk of heart disease and stroke for countless people despite the wellknown negative health effects of the typical american diet statins may well render death by coronary artery disease a rare event in the nottoodistant future subsequently the team lead by drs brown and goldstein elucidated the role of lipid modification of proteins protein prenylation in cancer in  he was awarded the louisa gross horwitz prize from columbia university together with michael s brown cowinner of  nobel prize in physiology or medicine in  goldstein also received national medal of science a highly acclaimed honor in the scientific world in the us in  their postdoctoral trainees xiaodong wang and michael briggs purified the sterol regulatory element binding proteins srebps since  drs goldstein brown and their colleagues have described the unexpectedly complex machinery by which cells maintain the necessary levels of fats and cholesterol in the face of varying environmental circumstances dr goldstein is a regental professor of the university of texas holds the julie and louis a beecherl distinguished chair in biomedical science and the paul j thomas chair in medicine frequently mentioned as a candidate for nationallyprominent positions in scientific administration dr goldstein like his colleague michael s brown elects to continue handson involvement with research together they lead a research team that typically includes a dozen doctoral and postdoctoral trainees he and his colleague are among the most highly cited scientists in the world for a look at dr goldsteins current research check out the brown and goldstein lab home key papers  expression of the familial hypercholesterolemia gene in heterozygotes mechanism for a dominant disorder in man science  jul   regulation of the activity of the low density lipoprotein receptor in human fibroblasts cell  nov  release of low density lipoprotein from its cell surface receptor by sulfated glycosaminoglycans cell  jan  receptormediated control of cholesterol metabolism science  jan   heterozygous familial hypercholesterolemia failure of normal allele to compensate for mutant allele at a regulated genetic locus cell  oct  analysis of a mutant strain of human fibroblasts with a defect in the internalization of receptorbound low density lipoprotein cell  dec pt   role of the coated endocytic vesicle in the uptake of receptorbound low density lipoprotein in human fibroblasts cell  mar  genetics of the ldl receptor evidence that the mutations affecting binding and internalization are allelic cell  nov  a mutation that impairs the ability of lipoprotein receptors to localise in coated pits on the cell surface of human fibroblasts nature  dec   immunocytochemical visualization of coated pits and vesicles in human fibroblasts relation to low density lipoprotein receptor distribution cell  nov  coated pits coated vesicles and receptormediated endocytosis nature  jun   ldl receptors in coated vesicles isolated from bovine adrenal cortex binding sites unmasked by detergent treatment cell  jul  regulation of plasma cholesterol by lipoprotein receptors science  may   monensin interrupts the recycling of low density lipoprotein receptors in human fibroblasts cell  may  posttranslational processing of the ldl receptor and its genetic disruption in familial hypercholesterolemia cell  oct  independent pathways for secretion of cholesterol and apolipoprotein e by macrophages science  feb   recycling receptors the roundtrip itinerary of migrant membrane proteins cell  mar  the ldl receptor locus in familial hypercholesterolemia multiple mutations disrupt transport and processing of a membrane receptor cell  mar  depletion of intracellular potassium arrests coated pit formation and receptormediated endocytosis in fibroblasts cell  may  increase in membrane cholesterol a possible trigger for degradation of hmg coa reductase and crystalloid endoplasmic reticulum in ut cells cell  apr  nucleotide sequence of hydroxymethylglutaryl coenzyme a reductase a glycoprotein of endoplasmic reticulum nature  apr   domain map of the ldl receptor sequence homology with the epidermal growth factor precursor cell  jun  hmg coa reductase a negatively regulated gene with unusual promoter and  untranslated regions cell  aug  the human ldl receptor a cysteinerich protein with multiple alu sequences in its mrna cell  nov  mutation in ldl receptor alualu recombination deletes exons encoding transmembrane and cytoplasmic domains science  jan   the ldl receptor gene a mosaic of exons shared with different proteins science  may   cassette of eight exons shared by genes for ldl receptor and egf precursor science  may   membranebound domain of hmg coa reductase is required for sterolenhanced degradation of the enzyme cell  may  internalizationdefective ldl receptors produced by genes with nonsense and frameshift mutations that truncate the cytoplasmic domain cell  jul   end of hmg coa reductase gene contains sequences responsible for cholesterolmediated inhibition of transcription cell  aug  scavenger cell receptor shared nature  aug   a receptormediated pathway for cholesterol homeostasis science  apr   the jd mutation in familial hypercholesterolemia amino acid substitution in cytoplasmic domain impedes internalization of ldl receptors cell  apr   deletion in cysteinerich region of ldl receptor impedes transport to cell surface in whhl rabbit science  jun   duplication of seven exons in ldl receptor gene caused by alualu recombination in a subject with familial hypercholesterolemia cell  mar    bp element from ldl receptor gene confers endproduct repression by sterols when inserted into viral tk promoter cell  mar   aciddependent ligand dissociation and recycling of ldl receptor mediated by growth factor homology region nature  apr   overexpression of low density lipoprotein ldl receptor eliminates ldl from plasma in transgenic mice science  mar   inhibition of purified pras farnesylprotein transferase by cysaax tetrapeptides cell  jul   dietinduced hypercholesterolemia in mice prevention by overexpression of ldl receptors science  nov   protein farnesyltransferase and geranylgeranyltransferase share a common alpha subunit cell  may   cdna cloning and expression of the peptidebinding beta subunit of rat pras farnesyltransferase the counterpart of yeast dprram cell  jul   purification of component a of rab geranylgeranyl transferase possible identity with the choroideremia gene product cell  sep   kochs postulates for cholesterol cell  oct   cdna cloning of component a of rab geranylgeranyl transferase and demonstration of its role as a rab escort protein cell  jun   srebp a basichelixloophelixleucine zipper protein that controls transcription of the low density lipoprotein receptor gene cell  oct   molecular characterization of a membrane transporter for lactate pyruvate and other monocarboxylates implications for the cori cycle cell  mar   srebp a membranebound transcription factor released by sterolregulated proteolysis cell  apr   sterolregulated release of srebp from cell membranes requires two sequential cleavages one within a transmembrane segment cell  jun   sterol resistance in cho cells traced to point mutation in srebp cleavageactivating protein cell  nov   the srebp pathway regulation of cholesterol metabolism by proteolysis of a membranebound transcription factor cell  may   transportdependent proteolysis of srebp relocation of site protease from golgi to er obviates the need for srebp transport to golgi cell  dec   regulated intramembrane proteolysis a control mechanism conserved from bacteria to humans cell  feb   regulated step in cholesterol feedback localized to budding of scap from er membranes cell  aug   crucial step in cholesterol homeostasis sterols promote binding of scap to insig a membrane protein that facilitates retention of srebps in er cell  aug  see also stormie jones category american biochemists   this article is licensed under the gnu free documentation license it uses material from the wikipedia article josephlgoldstein a list of authors is available in wikipedia topics az  a b c d e f g h i j k l m n o p q r s t u v w x y z all topics to top about chemiede chemiede information service gmbh runs specialist scientific internet portals the secret to our success we are familiar with what